{"id":3203,"date":"2022-11-01T13:20:17","date_gmt":"2022-11-01T13:20:17","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/?page_id=3203"},"modified":"2023-08-25T17:25:15","modified_gmt":"2023-08-25T17:25:15","slug":"workshops","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/workshops\/","title":{"rendered":"Workshops"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><span class=\"dropcap\">The ZCMP<\/span> workshops built on each other over a period of eight months to create the conditions for developing trust among a diverse group of participants who had experienced the pandemic in radically different ways. Through acting exercises and games; storytelling, writing and art-making; and through discussions about how we can promote social change, we aimed to work through loss, enable healing, and create community. We were able to share our stories and express feelings and thoughts many of us had not had the space to articulate, even to ourselves. Different collaborative projects and exercises allowed us to connect with each other in creative and even playful ways.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">\u201cI like being seen,\u201d one participant said. \u201cI like trusting,\u201d said another.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">What was the thinking behind our workshops? How did each work, and how did they build on each other? How did each address the particular challenges posed by the COVID-19 pandemic and the inequalities permeating our communities? The following descriptions, analyses, images and videos convey our thinking and methods for re-connecting with others around us and sharing our experiences and hopes. We call this our &#8220;toolkit.&#8221; In the final Train the Trainers workshop, George Emilio Sanchez explains to those who might want to continue the practices with others what it means to be a good facilitator and workshop leader.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"341\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/rehearsalsmain.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3603\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/rehearsalsmain.jpg 512w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/rehearsalsmain-300x200.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Rehearsals for Change<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first goal of Rehearsals for Change is to nurture and develop&nbsp;<strong>trust<\/strong>&nbsp;among the participants. Beginning with a dive into the foundational exercises taken from &#8230;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/rehersals-for-change\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">visit<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/ZIP-CODES_MJ_WSGroup1_061_DDR-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3619\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/ZIP-CODES_MJ_WSGroup1_061_DDR-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/ZIP-CODES_MJ_WSGroup1_061_DDR-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/ZIP-CODES_MJ_WSGroup1_061_DDR-768x511.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/ZIP-CODES_MJ_WSGroup1_061_DDR-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/ZIP-CODES_MJ_WSGroup1_061_DDR-2048x1363.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/ZIP-CODES_MJ_WSGroup1_061_DDR-2000x1331.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Aqu\u00ed\/Here<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In Aqu\u00ed\/Here workshop participants have the opportunity to reflect and work collectively on their experiences during the pandemic through performance and mapping practices. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/aqui-here\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">visit<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Storytelling_header2_SJR-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3608\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Storytelling_header2_SJR-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Storytelling_header2_SJR-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Storytelling_header2_SJR-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Storytelling_header2_SJR-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Storytelling_header2_SJR-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Storytelling_header2_SJR-2000x1334.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Storytelling<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This three-part workshop beginning on Zoom due to Omicron, and moving to in-person in March, is guided participants to express their experiences of the pandemic through images and words. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/storytelling-2\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">visit<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-13 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Workshop-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2551\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Workshop-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Workshop-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Workshop-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Workshop.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Towards an Exhibition with I\u015f\u0131n \u00d6nol<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Small groups of participants worked together to think about how individual and group experiences with loss, and projects expressing these, can be amplified and transformed with &#8230;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/towards-an-exhibition\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">visit<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"682\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/211030-GeorgeWSGroup3-035-1024x682.jpeg\" alt=